column5: an interesting site indeed. seems pretty complete too. best to start from the home page:https://fishingoutposts.com/ thanks for posting this - it's in my favorites now. phish

That’s Adam Dempseys site and it’s packed with terrific information on all types of outposts and lodges, along with very reliable lake information. I once asked for information on a particular body of water and received two marked maps as well as a list of fifty locations for pike and walleye! Highly recommended.

Glad to hear you might get some use of the site! Unfortunately, I have neglected the site a bit too much lately. It's not entirely complete and the filter is not working properly. I hope to fix and update it, but I keep getting sidetracked. Some big outfitters are still not listed, basically most outfitters from T onward alphabetically.
Adam,Thanks for the site and it’s in my favorites as it’s really good. Glad to hear on the filter as I thought it was something I was doing wrong.
